  "prompt": "In one episode of Impractical Jokers, Murr married Sal's sister for Sal's punishment. Is it true and did it actually happen or was it a publicity gimmick?",
  "response": "Yes, it did happen! In the episode \"Speak of the Devil\" from Season 4 of **Impractical Jokers**, Murr was forced to marry Sal's sister, **Jenny Vulcano**, as part of his punishment. The wedding took place in front of a live audience, complete with vows, a ceremony officiated by a real judge, and even a reception. \n\nWhile it was a real legal ceremony (meaning it was technically legal under the law), it was not a binding, long-term marriage. Murr and Jenny annulled the marriage shortly after the episode aired, confirming that it was done purely for the show and the punishment. It was a genuine event for the sake of the show, but it wasn\u2019t intended to be a lasting marital commitment. So, while it wasn\u2019t a publicity gimmick in the traditional sense, it was definitely an over-the-top, comedy-driven moment for the show.",
